                            <comment id="17693837" author="jzhuge" created="Mon, 27 Feb 2023 07:52:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks like a regression from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-41188&quot; title=&quot;Set executorEnv OMP_NUM_THREADS to be spark.task.cpus by default for spark executor JVM processes&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-41188&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-41188&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; where it removed the code that sets the default OMP_NUM_THREADS from PythonRunner.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Its PR assumes the code can be moved to SparkContext, unfortunately `SparkContext#executorEnvs` is only used by StandaloneSchedulerBackend for Spark&apos;s standalone cluster manager, thus the PR broke YARN as shown in the test case above, probably Mesos as well but I don&apos;t have a way to test.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17694145" author="apachespark" created="Mon, 27 Feb 2023 19:23:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;User &apos;jzhuge&apos; has created a pull request for this issue:&lt;br/&gt;
